column38: Pillsbury believes that there are some things at home that can't be bought. You can't buy holiday traditions like baking biscuits together, putting the angel tree topper on a Christmas tree or taking a family photo. column38: After a dreary evening commute back to her apartment, singer-songwriter FKA twigs decides she needs to unwind. When the track kicks into gear, twigs' dance throughout her flat causes her walls, tables and furniture shift into arrays of long, colorful streaks that mimic her movements. At the end of a phantasmagoric corridor, the musician's reflection steps out of a mirror, and the two twirl around in ecstasy until the avant-pop artist comes to a rest face-up on her couch. This, Apple says, is "the new sound of home."

column38: Tom Brady calls his best buddy Rob Gronkowski for advice on what his next move should be after leaving Boston. In Florida, Rob Gronkowski urges Brady to retire, which would allow his friend to "tamp down the stress." He even likens retirement to "winning another championship" and comments that the deal sounds so good he may even join Brady. However, Tom Brady heard things differently on his spotty network. Brady heard his friend urge him to go to Tampa Bay and try for another championship, noting that he'd be a soft and weak man for not going through with it.
